# Throw `RpcError` Instead Of `Error`

- Do not throw `new Error(...)` in new or edited backend code.
- Always throw `new RpcError(code, message)` (`firebase/functions/src/Utils/RpcError.ts`) so error handling is consistent across the API boundary.
- Choose the code that matches intent: `NOT_FOUND`, `INVALID_ARGUMENT`, `UNAUTHENTICATED`, `PERMISSION_DENIED`, `FAILED_PRECONDITION`, `INTERNAL`.

```typescript
// ❌ Avoid
throw new Error("Project not found")

// ✅ Prefer
throw new RpcError("NOT_FOUND", "Project not found")
```
